news.title: Gurugram: Toll-free number for property ID errors
news.para: The complaints from the call centre will be directed to the officials concerned so that people don’t have to run from pillar to post to get their grievances resolved.

news.title: Bengaluru: This fiscal, BBMP records 50% rise in property tax collection
news.para: According to data shared by the urban local body, the Palike collected Rs 1,786.2 crore till May 26, an increase of 84.2% as against 2020-2021 (May 26).

news.title: In Pune, joint property ownership goes up to 88%; maximum in Maharashtra
news.para: A special initiative by the Pune Zilla Parishad has entailed that out of the 9.27 lakh property cards, nearly 8.15 lakh have names of both men and women.

news.title: Pucca house still a distant dream for half of Madhya Pradesh families
news.para: In the state, only 45% households have a pucca house, showed the fifth round of National Family and Health Survey. In case of rural areas, only 32.6% of households have a pucca house in Madhya Pradesh with over 70% population in these areas, showed survey.

news.title: Maharashtra: Collectors told to speed up MahaRERA recovery orders
news.para: Overall, MahaRERA has listed recovery warrants worth Rs 702. 49 crore against errant developers in 13 districts of the state.

news.title: Mumbai: Court denies pre-arrest bail to directors of K D Developers
news.para: As per the case details, the accused were constructing Ruparel Orion, a residential tower in suburban Chembur. The complainant claimed that he had booked a flat in the building and had also convinced his colleagues purchase flats there.

news.title: Ajnara loses land over non-payment of dues after 11 years in Greater Noida
news.para: "Ajnara Realtech had purchased 72,962 square metres of land from GNIDA in 2011 for about Rs 84.34 crore. After paying 10 per cent of the total money, an installment of 90 per cent of the amount was made which were to be paid twice every year," GNIDA's office on special duty (OSD) Soumya Srivastava said.

news.title: Shriram Properties posts Rs 64.4 crore profit in Jan-Mar quarter
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 236.5 crore in the fourth quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 157.33 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Hong Kong home prices reverse three-month drop to climb 0.5% in April
news.para: Prices in what survey company Demographia ranked the world's most unaffordable housing market, climbed 0.5% in April from the previous month, according to official data, compared with a revised 0.6% fall in March.

news.title: Evergrande discussing staggered payments, debt-to-equity swaps for $19 billion offshore bonds
news.para: Evergrande's entire $22.7 billion worth of offshore debt including loans and private bonds is deemed to be in default after missing payment obligations late last year. It said in March that it will unveil a preliminary debt restructuring proposal by the end of July.

news.title: China's first residential REITs to be launched soon
news.para: Stock exchanges in Shanghai and Shenzhen each accepted an application for residential REITs backed by rental incomes from affordable housing, exchange filings show.

news.title: India Cements set to hike price by Rs 55 per bag
news.para: ​“There are 40 different brands selling cement in the region in the price range of Rs 320 – Rs 400 per bag. Our products are premium and we had always priced it higher in the range of Rs 360 and above,” he said.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body files complaints against 18 commercial buildings
news.para: The city civic body has filed complaints against builders and managements of 18 commercial properties for failing to comply with fire safety norms.

news.title: Over 100 deeds registered at Kanpur development body's registry camp
news.para: The deeds of only those allottees were registered who had completed all the formalities before registration. KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh introduced a new tradition for registering plots.

news.title: Ludhiana: Property owners, councillor oppose demolition drive in Model Town
news.para: As the situation turned stormy, senior town planner Surinder Singh Bindra reached the spot in support of his staff. The councillor accused Bindra and his officials of encouraging encroachments in other parts of city.
